                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.199/57: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-22T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 22, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>B–384. Your 398, November 20, 1 p.m. We are not, of course, prepared to accept a
                    representative of General Franco as an “ambassador” or “diplomatic agent”. We
                    feel that the continued presence of our consular officers in territory under the
                    control of General Franco is so obviously in the interest of all concerned that
                    we assume no question will be raised about it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
